verbLexeme: 1. Of soldiers, to walk with quick regular steps, as a group. English = march.
2. Especially of soldiers, to march together in front of important people or the public. English = parade.
nominalLexeme: 1. Of soldiers, the action of walking together with quick regular steps, as a group. English = march.
2. An occasion on which people, especially soldiers, march together in front of important people or the public. English = parade.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: lots of legs, in rows, moving forward.
